div.div:
Backup
- Backup from mysql_ec2 server
- Upload to mysql_ec2 backup s3 bucket.
- Setup a Management (mgmt) Host with Percona Mysql installed on it.
- Restore the XtraDB backup taken earlier to the ec2 host.
- Table-by-table backup (separate for schema and data) from the mgmt host using mysqldump tool.

Restore to Aurora
- Using mysql client tool.
- Schema files for each table ~ few minutes
- Table Data
- Table-by-table parallel restoration
- meaning - 2000 connections made to the db at the same time to restore ~ couple of hours

- Enable Read-Only mode in mysql_ec2.

- Redeploy the repos affected.- Replication is stopped on Aurora
